### MERN Assignment API — manual smoke test
### Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension. Run requests top-to-bottom.
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health

### Register (multipart). Attach an image file to test the upload, or omit it.
# After this, check the server logs for the Ethereal email preview URL,
# open it, and click the verification link (hits /api/auth/verify-email).
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----boundary

------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="name"

Jane Doe
------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

jane@example.com
------boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="password"

Passw0rd123
------boundary--

### Verify email (paste the token from the email preview URL)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/verify-email?token=PASTE_TOKEN_HERE

### Login (save accessToken + refreshToken from the response)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "password": "Passw0rd123"
}

@accessToken = {{login.response.body.data.accessToken}}
@refreshToken = {{login.response.body.data.refreshToken}}

### List users — paginated + search
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users?page=1&limit=10&search=jane
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### My profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Update my profile
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane D."
}

### Refresh tokens
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### Forgot password
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane@example.com"
}

### Reset password (token from the reset email preview URL)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "PASTE_RESET_TOKEN_HERE",
  "password": "NewPassw0rd123"
}

### Delete a user — ADMIN ONLY (expect 403 with a non-admin token)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/users/SOME_USER_UUID
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Logout (revokes the refresh token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}
